# Tech Stack Rules

## Package Manager
Always use pnpm. Never npm or yarn.

## Imports — Always Use Path Aliases
import { something } from '@/lib/...'  ✅
import { something } from '../../../lib/...'  ❌

## Next.js Patterns
- Use Server Components by default — only add 'use client' when truly needed
- All data fetching in Server Components or Route Handlers
- Use next/server for middleware auth
- Streaming: use Vercel AI SDK's `streamText` or `createStreamableUI`

## Supabase
Server client (API routes, server components):
  import { createClient } from '@/lib/db/supabase/server'
  
Browser client (client components only):
  import { createClient } from '@/lib/db/supabase/client'

NEVER use the service_role key in client components.

## Drizzle ORM
- Schema lives in src/lib/db/schema.ts
- Queries in src/lib/db/queries/*.ts — one file per domain
- Always use typed queries — never raw SQL unless Drizzle can't express it
- Migrations: pnpm drizzle-kit generate → pnpm drizzle-kit migrate

## Zod Validation
- Every API route input validated with Zod before processing
- Every agent input/output type has a matching Zod schema in src/validation/schemas.ts
- Use z.infer<typeof schema> to derive TypeScript types — single source of truth

## Anthropic / Vercel AI SDK
- Import Anthropic SDK: import Anthropic from '@anthropic-ai/sdk'
- Import Vercel AI SDK: import { streamText, generateText } from 'ai'
- All calls must set: model, max_tokens, temperature (never use defaults silently)
- Always use streaming: streamText not generateText for user-facing responses

## LangGraph.js
- Graph definitions in src/lib/ai/agents/orchestrator.ts
- Each node is a pure async function: (state: PipelineState) => Partial<PipelineState>
- State is immutable — always return new partial state, never mutate
- Use typed edges — no string-typed edge conditions

## Langfuse Tracing
Every LLM call must be wrapped:
  const trace = langfuse.trace({ name: 'agent-name', userId })
  const generation = trace.generation({ name: 'prompt-name', model, input })
  // ... make LLM call
  generation.end({ output, usage })

## TanStack Query
- All server state via useQuery / useMutation
- Invalidate queries after mutations — never manually update cache
- Use suspense mode for loading states

## Zustand
- One store per domain: user-profile.store.ts, generation.store.ts
- Use slices pattern for large stores
- Never store derived state — compute it

## Error Handling
- All try/catch must handle the error meaningfully — no empty catch blocks
- API routes return consistent shape: { success: bool, data?: T, error?: string }
- Use Sentry.captureException for unexpected errors